text.section:
The underlying purposes and policies of this code shall be:
To simplify, clarify, and modernize the law governing purchasing by the Commonwealth;
To permit the continued development of purchasing policies and practices;
To make as consistent as possible the purchasing laws among the various states;
To provide for increased public confidence in the procedures followed in public procurement;
To insure the fair and equitable treatment of all persons who deal with the procurement system of the Commonwealth;
To provide increased economy in state procurement activities by fostering effective competition; and
To provide safeguards for the maintenance of a procurement system of quality and integrity.
